  "title": "Phlebotomist",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company’s Profile:</strong></p><p>Our client is a leading public healthcare institution that provides seamless, team-based care across all stages of a patient’s health journey. Serving a diverse community, they are committed to innovation, collaboration, and using technology to deliver person-centered, holistic care. Awarded as one of the Best Employers in 2025, they are looking for qualified individuals to join their dynamic environment dedicated to improving lives\nwithin the community.</p><p>Work Location: West side polyclinics</p><p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Provide fast, skillful and accurate blood collection for patients using venipuncture, capillary and heel-prick</li><li>Perform phlebotomy, ECG, spirometry in an accurate, efficient and professional way</li><li>Ensure compliance with infection control guidelines</li><li>Ensure 2 identifier is performed for every patient prior to collection before performing test for patients</li><li>Ensure proper documentation for traceability and in adherence to good documentation practices</li><li>Ensure compliance to workplace safety, hand hygiene and other applicable regulatory and accreditation requirements of the laboratory</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>At least 2 – 3 years’ experience with phlebotomy</li><li>Open to travelling around west side polyclinics when necessary </li><li>Any educational qualification in healthcare / Phlebotomy Certificate </li></ul><p><br />Interested candidates may <strong>whatsapp your resume to 8977 7062</strong>. Only shortlisted applicants will be contacted.</p><p><br />By submitting your personal data and/or resume, you give consent to the collection, use and disclosure of your personal data and/or resume by the company (or its agent) for the purpose of the processing and administration by company relating to this job application.</p><p>Cassie Chan | R2197426</p><p>EnviroDynamics Solutions Pte Ltd | EA No: 12C6285</p>",
